<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634152532785222467" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634273300728609555">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[The example]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>The snippet demonstrates look and feel of ScheduleBox with different view mode, hour format, first day of week and work hours. Click the radio buttons to change presentation. Drag slider to adjust work hours start and end time. Select a date in calendar to set first date shown by control.<br /><br />The example shows a few scheduled events, each event is an object of&nbsp;<em>ScheduleBoxEvent</em> class.<br />The event has <em>Start</em> and <em>End </em>DateTime properties, as well as <em>Subject (</em>string) property and <em>Tag</em> (object) property describing the event. The <em>Tag</em> property is general purpose property to carry additional information with event object.</p><p><strong>Double click</strong> an event to explore an event details. You can change event settings. The Tag property used to store a string, but could be any object. If Start/End date changed, the event will be shown such that the Start date is first date shown in the ScheduleBox.</p><p>To implement opening of the editing form on event double click - added an event handler for&nbsp;ScheduleBox&nbsp;<strong>EventDoubleClick </strong>event.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[General Info]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>The Visual WebGui <em>ScheduleBox </em>control contains the following properties to adjust the view:<br /><strong>HourFormat</strong><em> </em>&ndash; defines the displayed hours format<br /><strong>View</strong><em> </em>&ndash; defines the view mode for the ScheduleBox<br /><strong>FirstDayOfWeek</strong><em> </em>&ndash; defines the first day of week<br /><strong>FirstDate</strong><em> </em>&ndash; defines the first date of the ScheduleBox in displayed date range<br /><br />The ScheduleBox<em> HourFormat </em>property value can be: <br /><strong>Clock12H </strong>&ndash; displays 12 hours format<br /><strong>Clock24H </strong>&ndash; displays 24 hours format<br /><br />The ScheduleBox <em>View</em> property value can be:<br /><strong>Week </strong>&ndash; to display business week without weekend<br /><strong>FullWeek </strong>&ndash; to display seven days, where the first date set by the FirstDate property<br /><strong>FullMonth </strong>&ndash; to display full month, where the first date set by the FirstDate property<br /><strong>Day </strong>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;to display only one day, where  the date set by the FirstDate property<br /><strong>Month </strong>&ndash; to display month with merged days of weekend.</p><p>The ScheduleBox<em> FirstDayOfWeek </em>property values:<br /><strong>Monday </strong>&ndash; defines that first day of week is Monday<br /><strong>Sunday </strong>&ndash; defines that first day of week is Sunday</p>]]></Paragraph>
  </Nodes>
</Data>